enhanced_by.reason: Both methods require a BaseProviders instance for generating ID numbers.
The generateInvalid method relies on the getPattern method to obtain a pattern for generating invalid SSNs.
The generateInvalid method uses the isValidEnZASsn method to check if the generated SSN is valid before returning it as invalid.
The isValidEnZASsn method relies on the calculateChecksum method to validate the SSN, indirectly affecting the generateInvalid method.
